    "text": "Normal combo — you stacked two things that both push heart rate up and, just as importantly, both make you notice it. Caffeine nudges heart rate upward and heightens your awareness of each beat, so sitting still during rest sets with a double espresso on board, feeling every thump is expected rather than alarming. Layer intervals on top — your session averaged 164 bpm with a peak of 181 bpm — and a racing feeling through the whole workout makes complete sense. Your background picture is calm too: this morning's resting heart rate was 58 bpm, right at its 57.6 baseline. The combination that would deserve an actual check-up is different: a racing or irregular heartbeat at rest with no caffeine or exercise in the picture, or palpitations alongside chest pain or faintness. An espresso-fuelled interval night isn't that.",
